Juventus have released their squad that will tackle Napoli in tonight’s Italian Super Cup final at Stadio Città del Tricolore in Reggio Emilia, Italy. The Serie A champions released a list of 21 players via its website. Juventus head to the game following a 2-0 defeat against Inter Milan in the Serie A in their last fixture on Sunday, while Napoli defeated Fiorentina 6-0. Juventus’ squad against Napoli: Goalkeepers: Szczęsny, Pinsoglio, Buffon. Defenders: Chiellini, Danilo, Bonucci, Di Pardo, Dragusin, Frabotta. Midfielders: Arthur, Ramsey, Mckennie, Chiesa, Rabiot, Bentancur, Bernardeschi, Fagioli, Kulusevski, Ranocchia. Forwards: Cristiano Ronaldo, Alvaro Morata. The kick-off time for Juventus vs Napoli is 9 pm.